{"id":"1412.5427","submitter":"Virginia D'Auria","authors":"Lutfi Arif Ngah, Olivier Alibart, Laurent Labont\\'e, Virginia D'Auria,\n  S\\'ebastien Tanzilli","title":"Ultra-fast heralded single photon source based on telecom technology","comments":"5 pages, 2 figures","journal-ref":"Laser and Photon. Rev., vol. 9, L1-L5 (2015)","doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The realization of an ultra-fast source of heralded single photons emitted at\nthe wavelength of 1540 nm is reported. The presented strategy is based on\nstate-of-the-art telecom technology, combined with off-the-shelf fiber\ncomponents and waveguide non-linear stages pumped by a 10 GHz repetition rate\nlaser. The single photons are heralded at a rate as high as 2.1 MHz with a\nheralding efficiency of 42%. Single photon character of the source is inferred\nby measuring the second-order autocorrelation function. For the highest\nheralding rate, a value as low as 0.023 is found. This not only proves\nnegligible multi-photon contributions but also represents the best measured\nvalue reported to date for heralding rates in the MHz regime. These prime\nperformances, associated with a device-like configuration, are key ingredients\nfor both fast and secure quantum communication protocols.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 17 Dec 2014 15:08:27 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-03-19"}
